      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2024-06-07T14:06:41.544Z",
      "cooked": "<p>So I am not fully understanding\u2026   We need some kind of reference point(s).  If he does not know his power how can he doe that?  Also the  MINOURA V100 seems to have different settings, so we would need estimates for each setting unless he just sticks to one.</p>\n<p>I think this might be a better way to do it or could be pretty accurate.  Just get 2 reference points</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Find a speed that feels like the maximum you can do for 5 minutes, and write down the speed and go as long as you can</li>\n<li>Do the same thing but for 20 minutes in a separate test</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Then finally in addition to those 2 ref points, we need an approximation of your FTP.  Could be gotten based on an outdoor ride (even without a power meter), especially if you did a race or all out effort and we can estimate your drag and know your weight\u2026 Or could just be what systm or TR told you.</p>\n<p>But yes with regards to your idea <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/medtechcd\">@MedTechCD</a> is if he just had some different speed and power values from TR or Systm, we could compare and see about matching theres.</p>",
